  <description type="morphology">Stems 2.3–7(–9) dm, moderately to densely hirsute proximally, glabrous distally. Cauline leaves: blade conduplicate distally, margins entire or denticulate, surfaces hirsute. Racemes secund; rachis straight. Fruiting pedicels 3–10 mm, sparsely pubescent or glabrous. Flowers: sepals cream or pale yellow, 5–6 mm, glabrous or sparsely pubescent; petals white (without purple veins), 10–17 mm; adaxial filaments 7–10 mm. Fruits spreading to slightly reflexed, arcuate; valves glabrous or sparsely pubescent. 2n = 28.</description>
